  "playingCareerSummary": "Former Sri Lanka captain and one of the game's most elegant batters: 149 Tests (11,814 runs), 448 ODIs (12,650 runs). IPL playing career: Kings XI Punjab (2008), Kochi Tuskers Kerala (2011), Delhi Daredevils (2013-2015).",
  "bio": "The only person to win three IPL titles as Mumbai Indians head coach (2017, 2019, 2020). First joined as MI's batting consultant in 2015 before being elevated to head coach in 2017. Led MI through the most successful run in franchise history, including back-to-back titles in 2019-2020. Stepped down after the disastrous 2022 season and was replaced by Mark Boucher. Returned to the role in 2025 after Boucher's two seasons yielded limited success.",
